  "text": "Pixel-level text center line is proposed [CITATION_1] , since the center lines are far from each other. In [CITATION_2] , a prediction map indicating text lines is predicted. These text lines can be easily separated as they are not adjacent. To produce prediction for text instance, a binary map of text center line of a text instance is attached to the original input image and fed into a classification network. A saliency mask is generated indicating the detected text. However, this method involves several steps. The text-line generation step and the final prediction step can not be trained end-to-end, and error propagates.",
